Excellent posting.</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="10" relname="concession"> I am right handed</segment>
    <segment id="10" parent="15" relname="span"> but surrounded with lefties</segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="20" relname="span"> and I have never thought 
about the location of the numeric key pad.</segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="19" relname="span">

Mouses can be programmed for lefties</segment>
    <segment id="11" parent="3" relname="elaboration"> and this has been case for a long time.</segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="7" relname="span"> I am 
always surprised at the number of people who are not aware of this feature.</segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="16" relname="conjunction"> When I was 
a PC Tech </segment>
    <segment id="14" parent="16" relname="conjunction">and came accross a left handed user</segment>
    <segment id="12" parent="17" relname="span"> I would offer a left mouse set up for 
them.</segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="18" relname="span"> Well many people said they had gotten use to the right hand set up</segment>
    <segment id="13" parent="6" relname="elaboration"> and did not 
need to switch.

</segment>
